s.This highly original and creative study reconnects the law to its narrative roots by showing how and why stories become laws.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCriticism. 0aLaw and literature. 0aLawxPhilosophy. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLAW / Legal History.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269352440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442693524423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442693524.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK